25|$|<b>Virtual</b> <b>reality</b> (<b>VR)</b> games {{generally}} require {{players to}} use a special head-mounted unit that provides stereoscopic screens and motion tracking to immerse a player within virtual environment that responds to their head movements. Some VR systems include control units for the player's hands as to provide a direct way {{to interact with the}} virtual world. VR systems generally require a separate computer, console, or other processing device that couples with the head-mounted unit.|$|E
